to the editor re competing to make things worse by richard a epstein op ed sept 7 mr epstein aptly criticizes both candidates proposals to cover prescription drugs for the elderly the economies achieved by privatization versus the security afforded by government financed programs has become a partisan issue this is good fare for debating but the kiss of death for federal action why not enliven the debate over adding prescription drug coverage by throwing in controlled tax cutting for the elderly by giving the wealthy elderly a tax credit for their prescription coverage by paying for the prescription coverage of the poor and calculating a sliding scale for everyone else we might have an experimental stalking horse for subsequent medicare reform herbert s gross md rockville md sept 8 2000

